020package org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer;
021
022import static org.apiguardian.api.API.Status.DEPRECATED;
023import static org.apiguardian.api.API.Status.STABLE;
024
025import javax.lang.model.element.AnnotationMirror;
026import java.lang.annotation.Annotation;
027
028import org.apiguardian.api.API;
029import org.tquadrat.foundation.annotation.ClassVersion;
030import org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer.internal.AnnotationSpecImpl;
031
032/**
033 *  The specification for a generated annotation on a declaration.
034 *
035 *  @author Square,Inc.
036 *  @modified Thomas Thrien - thomas.thrien@tquadrat.org
037 *  @version $Id: AnnotationSpec.java 1066 2023-09-28 19:51:53Z tquadrat $
038 *  @since 0.0.5
039 *
040 *  @UMLGraph.link
041 */
042@ClassVersion( sourceVersion = "$Id: AnnotationSpec.java 1066 2023-09-28 19:51:53Z tquadrat $" )
043@API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
044public sealed interface AnnotationSpec
045    permits AnnotationSpecImpl
046{
047        /*---------------*\
048    ====** Inner Classes **====================================================
049        \*---------------*/
050    /**
051     *  The specification of a builder for an instance of an implementation of
052     *  {@link AnnotationSpec}.
053     *
054     *  @author Square,Inc.
055     *  @modified Thomas Thrien - thomas.thrien@tquadrat.org
056     *  @version $Id: AnnotationSpec.java 1066 2023-09-28 19:51:53Z tquadrat $
057     *  @since 0.0.5
058     *
059     *  @UMLGraph.link
060     */
061    @SuppressWarnings( "InnerClassOfInterface" )
062    @ClassVersion( sourceVersion = "$Id: AnnotationSpec.java 1066 2023-09-28 19:51:53Z tquadrat $" )
063    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
064    public static sealed interface Builder
065        permits AnnotationSpecImpl.BuilderImpl
066    {
067            /*---------*\
068        ====** Methods **======================================================
069            \*---------*/
070        /**
071         *  Adds a building block.
072         *
073         *  @param  name    The name.
074         *  @param  format  The format for the
075         *      {@link CodeBlock}.
076         *  @param  args  The arguments for the
077         *      {@link CodeBlock}.
078         *  @return This {@code Builder} instance.
079         *
080         *  @see JavaComposer#codeBlockOf(String, Object...)
081         */
082        public default Builder addMember( final CharSequence name, final String format, final Object... args )
083        {
084            return addMember( name, false, format, args );
085        }   //  addMember()
086
087        /**
088         *  Adds a building block.
089         *
090         *  @param  name    The name.
091         *  @param  addDebugOutput  {@code true} if debug output should be
092         *      added to the generated code, {@code false} if not.
093         *  @param  format  The format for the
094         *      {@link CodeBlock}.
095         *  @param  args  The arguments for the
096         *      {@link CodeBlock}.
097         *  @return This {@code Builder} instance.
098         *
099         *  @see CodeBlock#of(String, Object...)
100         *  @since 0.0.6
101         *
102         *  @deprecated Got obsolete with the introduction of
103         *      {@link JavaComposer}.
104         */
105        @SuppressWarnings( "removal" )
106        @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
107        @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.6" )
108        public Builder addMember( final CharSequence name, final boolean addDebugOutput, final String format, final Object... args );
109
110        /**
111         *  Adds a building block.
112         *
113         *  @param  name    The name.
114         *  @param  codeBlock   The
115         *      {@link CodeBlock}
116         *      representing the new member.
117         *  @return This {@code Builder} instance.
118         */
119        public Builder addMember( final CharSequence name, final CodeBlock codeBlock );
120
121        /**
122         *  Creates the {@code AnnotationSpec} instance from the added members.
123         *
124         *  @return The built instance.
125         */
126        public AnnotationSpec build();
127
128        /**
129         *  Sets a flag that forces the inline presentation of the
130         *  annotation.<br>
131         *  <br>Inline:<pre><code>@Column(name = "updated_at", nullable = false)</code></pre>
132         *
133         *  Not inline:<pre><code>  @Column(
134         *      name = "updated_at",
135         *      nullable = false
136         *  )</code></pre>
137         *
138         *  @param  flag    {@code true} for the forced inline presentation,
139         *      {@code false} for the multi-line presentation.
140         *  @return This {@code Builder} instance.
141         */
142        public Builder forceInline( boolean flag );
143    }
144    //  interface Builder
145
146        /*---------*\
147    ====** Methods **==========================================================
148        \*---------*/
149    /**
150     *  Creates a builder for an instance of an implementation for
151     *  {@code AnnotationSpec} from the given
152     *  {@link ClassName}
153     *  instance.
154     *
155     *  @param  type    The class name.
156     *  @return The new builder.
157     *
158     *  @deprecated Replaced by
159     *      {@link JavaComposer#annotationBuilder(ClassName)}.
160     */
161    @SuppressWarnings( "removal" )
162    @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
163    @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.5" )
164    public static Builder builder( final ClassName type )
165    {
166        return AnnotationSpecImpl.builder( type );
167    }   //  builder()
168
169    /**
170     *  Creates a builder for an instance of an implementation for
171     *  {@code AnnotationSpec} from the given
172     *  {@link Class}
173     *  instance.
174     *
175     *  @param  type    The class.
176     *  @return The new builder.
177     *
178     *  @deprecated Replaced by
179     *      {@link JavaComposer#annotationBuilder(ClassName)}.
180     */
181    @SuppressWarnings( "removal" )
182    @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
183    @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.5" )
184    public static Builder builder( final Class<?> type )
185    {
186        return AnnotationSpecImpl.builder( type );
187    }   //  builder()
188
189    /**
190     *  {@inheritDoc}
191     */
192    @Override
193    public boolean equals( final Object o );
194
195    /**
196     *  Creates an instance of {@code AnnotationSpec} from the given
197     *  {@link Annotation}
198     *  instance.
199     *
200     *  @param  annotation  The annotation.
201     *  @return The new instance of {@code AnnotationSpec}.
202     *
203     *  @deprecated Replaced by
204     *      {@link JavaComposer#createAnnotation(Annotation)}.
205     */
206    @SuppressWarnings( "removal" )
207    @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
208    @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.5" )
209    public static AnnotationSpec get( final Annotation annotation )
210    {
211        return AnnotationSpecImpl.get( annotation );
212    }   //  get()
213
214    /**
215     *  Creates an instance of {@code AnnotationSpec} from the given
216     *  {@link Annotation}
217     *  instance.
218     *
219     *  @param  annotation  The annotation.
220     *  @param  includeDefaultValues    {@code true} to include the
221     *      annotation's default values, {@code false} to ignore them.
222     *  @return The new instance of {@code AnnotationSpec}.
223     *
224     *  @deprecated Replaced by
225     *      {@link JavaComposer#createAnnotation(Annotation,boolean)}.
226     */
227    @SuppressWarnings( "removal" )
228    @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
229    @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.5" )
230    public static AnnotationSpec get( final Annotation annotation, final boolean includeDefaultValues )
231    {
232        @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
233        final var retValue = AnnotationSpecImpl.get( annotation, includeDefaultValues );
234
235        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
236        return retValue;
237    }   //  get()
238
239    /**
240     *  Creates an instance of {@code AnnotationSpec} from the given
241     *  {@link AnnotationMirror}
242     *  instance.
243     *
244     *  @param  annotation  The annotation mirror.
245     *  @return The new instance of {@code AnnotationSpec}.
246     *
247     *  @deprecated Replaced by
248     *      {@link JavaComposer#createAnnotation(AnnotationMirror)}.
249     */
250    @SuppressWarnings( "removal" )
251    @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
252    @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.5" )
253    public static AnnotationSpec get( final AnnotationMirror annotation )
254    {
255        @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
256        final var retValue = AnnotationSpecImpl.get( annotation );
257
258        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
259        return retValue;
260    }   //  get()
261
262    /**
263     *  {@inheritDoc}
264     */
265    @Override
266    public int hashCode();
267
268    /**
269     *  Creates a new builder that is initialised with the components of this
270     *  annotation.
271     *
272     *  @return The new builder.
273     */
274    public Builder toBuilder();
275
276    /**
277     *  {@inheritDoc}
278     */
279    @Override
280    public String toString();
281}
282//  interface AnnotationSpec
283
